cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.RO

The paper deals with the application of computer vision and deep neural networks for the detection, segmentation, and tracking of grape clusters in agricultural images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of deep neural networks for this task also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of image annotation and tracking, which could potentially fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.RO (Robotics).
